main event: A witness observed an unidentified white object moving across the eastern sky over Warrensville Heights, Ohio on May 10, 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed through binoculars and appeared to be a rectangular-shaped object with four smaller objects in close proximity.
The object remained motionless for about 10 seconds before moving at a steady speed across the sky over a 4 minute 32 second period.
The object was as bright as a 1st or 2nd magnitude star, with the witness unable to determine its actual size or speed.
Additional sightings of unidentified objects were reported in the Cleveland, Ohio area over several days around the May 10, 1964 incident.
The report was investigated by Project Blue Book, with the object ultimately identified as the satellite ECHO.
